1. Personal and Educational Use
The use of compiled LITH versions (Executables / Binaries) is entirely free, including within a company for commercial projects. You may use the tool to host and serve your web applications or assist your development workflow without any payment to FomaDev.

2. Contributions (Fork & Pull Request)
Forks are authorized ONLY for contributing to the official FomaDev project. Any improvements must be submitted via a Pull Request. By contributing, you agree that your code will be integrated under this same license.

3. Commercial Use and Competition (PAID)
A paid commercial license is MANDATORY for the following cases:
- Selling, distributing, or republishing a modified version of this server's source code on any platform or repository.
- Integrating LITH source code directly into another commercial software, proprietary web server, or development tool.
- Creating a paid commercial service or derivative product based on the LITH engine.
- Developing derivative products based on this source code.

4. Prohibition of Independent Forks
Maintaining a separate version (permanent Fork) of this project to bypass FomaDev's authority is strictly prohibited.

5. Licensing Contact
To obtain commercial authorization or negotiate an exploitation license, contact Fordi (FomaDev) directly.